1
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:02,767
<i> Cheska, what's wrong?</i>

2
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:04,767
<i>Martin, help! Someone's
chasing me!</i>

3
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:06,533
- [SCREAMING]
- [BLADE SWISHES]

4
00:00:06,667 --> 00:00:08,800
<i> Gio, hurry! Let's go!</i>

5
00:00:08,933 --> 00:00:10,833
- [SCREAMING]
- [CHAIN RATTLING]

6
00:00:10,967 --> 00:00:12,800
[THUDDING]

7
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:14,400
<i> Where's my map?!</i>

8
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:15,800
- [LEON SCREAMING]
- [HIT LANDS]

9
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:17,067
[SANDRO GROANS]

10
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:19,833
Tell them that Sandro is alive.

11
00:00:19,967 --> 00:00:21,200
Let's get out of here together.

12
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:22,633
- [SANDRO GRUNTS]
- [FLESH SQUELCHES]

13
00:00:22,767 --> 00:00:25,467
- [SANDRO GRUNTING]
- [KIKO SCREAMING, GROANING]

14
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,300
- [KIKO SCREAMS]
- [THUDS]

15
00:00:27,433 --> 00:00:28,400
[GRUNTS IN PAIN]

16
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:29,867
- [BLADE SWISHES]
- [KIKO GRUNTS]

17
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,033
- [SANDRO GRUNTING]
- [BLADE SWISHES]

18
00:00:32,167 --> 00:00:33,900
[KIKO COUGHING]

19
00:00:34,067 --> 00:00:36,233
- [FLESH SQUELCHING]
- [BLADE SWISHING]

20
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:38,333
<i> Kiko's in danger.</i>

21
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:39,567
<i> What?!</i>

22
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:41,500
<i> He didn't reply anymore!</i>

23
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:44,133
Kiko! Kiko, stay with us please!

24
00:00:44,267 --> 00:00:46,633
<i>Kiko, don't give up!
Don't give up, Kiko!</i>

25
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:48,667
<i> Kiko, please hold on!</i>

26
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:51,167
<i>Please, take care
of my brother!</i>

27
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:54,733
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

28
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:57,967
[CHESKA] No!
That's not true!

29
00:00:58,100 --> 00:01:00,033
Raphie, please tell me
you're joking.

30
00:01:00,167 --> 00:01:01,633
You're just playing
a prank on me, right?

31
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:03,667
Raphie, this isn't something
to joke about.

32
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:04,867
[CRYING] I'm sorry, Cheska.

33
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,500
What are you saying sorry for?!

34
00:01:06,633 --> 00:01:08,233
Hey, I'm not in the mood
for jokes right now!

35
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:09,667
Tell me the truth!
[CRYING]

36
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:12,167
No! No! Let me go!

37
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:15,267
Why are you comforting me?!
There's no need to!

38
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,333
What... what do you mean
you're sorry?

39
00:01:17,467 --> 00:01:19,567
Hey, what happened
to my brother?

40
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:22,233
Raphie, where--
where's my brother?

41
00:01:22,367 --> 00:01:23,600
Where's Kiko?!

42
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:24,867
Where's my brother?!

43
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,067
He's at the hospital
in critical condition.

44
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,600
Hospital?

45
00:01:28,733 --> 00:01:30,467
Critical condition?

46
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:32,900
Are you hearing this?

47
00:01:33,033 --> 00:01:34,867
- Let me go!
- Cheska, wait!

48
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Cheska!

49
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:43,967
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

50
00:02:36,967 --> 00:02:42,333
[MONITOR BEEPING IN DISTANCE]

51
00:02:42,467 --> 00:02:43,600
[SIGHS]

52
00:02:44,867 --> 00:02:47,000
[INHALES SHARPLY, SIGHS]

53
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:53,167
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

54
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:55,233
[JUSTIN SIGHS]

55
00:02:57,067 --> 00:02:58,600
Where's Leon?

56
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,567
I want to see him!
Where's your brother?

57
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:03,433
-They're treating him right now.
- Where is he?!

58
00:03:03,567 --> 00:03:04,633
He's undergoing surgery.

59
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:06,333
[SOBBING, PANTING]

60
00:03:06,467 --> 00:03:08,700
I'm seeing him for
the first time in a long while.

61
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:12,400
I don't know what I'll do
if something bad happens to him.

62
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:13,767
We don't know for sure, Ma.

63
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:16,333
All we can do for now
is to pray for him.

64
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:18,567
[FRIDA BREATHING HEAVILY]

65
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:20,467
- Just take a seat first.
- [CHESKA SOBBING] Kiko?

66
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,400
Kiko? Wh-- where's Kiko?

67
00:03:23,567 --> 00:03:25,633
My brother? Kiko!

68
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:27,900
- Kiko? Where's Kiko?
- Cheska... Cheska!

69
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:29,033
Where's-- Where's my brother?

70
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,500
He's undergoing surgery
right now.

71
00:03:30,633 --> 00:03:32,333
The doctors will save him, okay?

72
00:03:32,467 --> 00:03:34,733
What? What?!

73
00:03:34,867 --> 00:03:37,600
Gio! Martin! What?!

74
00:03:37,733 --> 00:03:39,533
Guys, what happened?!

75
00:03:39,667 --> 00:03:41,867
[SOBBING] Where's my brother?
What--

76
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,200
what happened to him? Who--
who did this to him?!

77
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:46,867
What on earth happened?!

78
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,700
[CHESKA] Kiko! What happened,
Martin?

79
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:52,167
We don't know.

80
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,933
We just saw him and Leon
in the woods.

81
00:03:57,067 --> 00:03:59,133
- The woods...
- Until...

82
00:03:59,267 --> 00:04:00,333
The woods where?

83
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:02,867
Near the hotel?

84
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:05,933
The woods near the hotel?

85
00:04:08,233 --> 00:04:10,633
The reason he went there
was because...

86
00:04:10,767 --> 00:04:12,767
he thought I was there!

87
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:15,967
It's all because of me!
This happened 'cause of me!

88
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:18,700
Ches-- Cheska, don't say that.

89
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:20,767
It's my fault
this happened to him!

90
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:23,100
We didn't know
this would happen, okay?

91
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:24,967
- Kiko, sorry...
- We didn't know--

92
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:27,933
He went to the woods
for me, Martin!

93
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:32,367
Kiko, I'm sorry! I'm so sorry!

94
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:39,333
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

95
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:46,300
[MONITOR BEEPING]

96
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:08,233
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

97
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:27,633
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES,
FADES]

98
00:05:27,767 --> 00:05:29,167
- [PHONE RINGING]
- [CLICKS TONGUE, SIGHS]

99
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:30,867
Hello, Cheska?

100
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:33,867
[CHESKA] Ma, you have to come
to the island.

101
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,500
Are you crying?

102
00:05:36,633 --> 00:05:37,833
What happened?

103
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:41,767
Ma, you have to come here.
[SOBBING]

104
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,033
Cheska, what's wrong?!
Answer me properly!

105
00:05:46,167 --> 00:05:48,100
You'll really get it from me!

106
00:05:48,533 --> 00:05:50,167
Ma, Kiko is...

107
00:05:52,367 --> 00:05:54,067
Ki-- Kiko is...

108
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:57,433
Ki-- Kiko's in a critical
condition, Ma...

109
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:59,233
So-- sorry, Ma...

110
00:06:00,167 --> 00:06:03,033
You have to come here, Ma.

111
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:06,867
<i> Please come here, Ma.</i>

112
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,400
You have to get here
right away, please!

113
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:11,567
Kiko is...

114
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:14,433
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:06:14,567 --> 00:06:16,033
[CHESKA] It's about Kiko, Ma.

116
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:18,567
Ma? Hello, Ma?

117
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:22,067
[VOICE BREAKING] I'm here...

118
00:06:23,533 --> 00:06:24,833
I'm here...

119
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:28,533
Wait...

120
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:30,400
wait for me.

121
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,900
I'll go.

122
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:37,700
Be careful, okay?
Get here quickly, please.

123
00:06:38,133 --> 00:06:40,500
I need you by my side, Ma.

124
00:06:41,133 --> 00:06:43,733
[CHESKA]<i> Please come here, Ma.
</i> Hurry.

125
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:46,300
<i> Please, hurry. Hurry!</i>

126
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,667
[THUDS]

127
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:56,833
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:07,667
[MARTIN WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

129
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,733
I'm sorry...

130
00:07:08,867 --> 00:07:11,067
Cheska, Cheska! Martin!

131
00:07:11,367 --> 00:07:12,533
Where's Kiko?

132
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,567
How's Kiko doing?

133
00:07:14,733 --> 00:07:15,667
He's undergoing surgery.

134
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,200
Huh?

135
00:07:17,567 --> 00:07:18,433
Cheska...

136
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:20,333
- [CHESKA SOBBING]
- Cheska, I'm sorry...

137
00:07:20,467 --> 00:07:22,000
Trixie, come with me.

138
00:07:22,133 --> 00:07:23,967
- Take a seat first.
- Here.

139
00:07:25,133 --> 00:07:27,967
[MARTIN BREATHES DARPLY]

140
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:31,600
[MARTIN EXHALES DEEPLY]

141
00:07:31,733 --> 00:07:33,900
Because you disobeyed
my orders...

142
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:37,400
look at what happened.

143
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:43,000
[VOICE BREAKING] Martin...

144
00:07:43,633 --> 00:07:44,800
Martin, I'm-- I'm sorry,

145
00:07:44,933 --> 00:07:47,167
we-- we just wanted to help.

146
00:07:48,567 --> 00:07:50,000
To help, again?

147
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:52,467
Look at what happened, Trixie.

148
00:07:54,767 --> 00:07:56,367
So, please.

149
00:07:57,167 --> 00:07:59,700
Listen to me when it comes
to things like this.

150
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,367
[GIO] Martin.

151
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:03,767
[TRIXIE WHISPERING] I'm sorry...

152
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:08,667
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

153
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:13,267
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

154
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:15,167
Just understand where
your brother's coming from.

155
00:08:16,633 --> 00:08:18,033
[GIO] Hm?

156
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:29,567
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

157
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:32,833
- [MONITOR BEEPING]
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:08:32,967 --> 00:08:34,100
[DOCTOR] Pressure's dropping.

159
00:08:34,233 --> 00:08:36,400
We're losing him.
Start compression now!

160
00:08:38,867 --> 00:08:40,300
[NURSE] He's bleeding
internally.

161
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:43,533
[DOCTOR] No pulse.
Worsening compression.

162
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:47,733
[DOCTOR] Check rhythm.
Still V-fib.

163
00:08:47,867 --> 00:08:50,400
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [MONITOR BEEPING CONTINUES]

164
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,167
Sir... Sir.

165
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:58,067
There is no CCTV
in the area.

166
00:08:59,167 --> 00:09:00,600
Look around.

167
00:09:00,733 --> 00:09:03,233
Whoever did that to the Almazans
has definitely gotten away

168
00:09:03,367 --> 00:09:04,800
Why don't we search outside?

169
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:06,667
It doesn't matter.

170
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,733
Let Banal and the others know.

171
00:09:09,867 --> 00:09:11,600
Talk to the guests
who are checked in

172
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:13,233
and ask them
what they were doing

173
00:09:13,367 --> 00:09:14,700
at the time the crime occurred.

174
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,400
We're wasting our time, Syvera.

175
00:09:16,533 --> 00:09:17,933
Wasting time?

176
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:21,067
Leon and Kiko have been stabbed!

177
00:09:24,033 --> 00:09:25,567
The murder weapon
might have been discarded

178
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:27,167
That's one of the things
we need to look for.

179
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:34,433
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

180
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,300
[SARI] Miss Luna....

181
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:37,967
- Eat first.
- Eat first.

182
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:40,533
Water? Water, Miss Luna?

183
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:43,867
Ms. Jade?

184
00:09:45,067 --> 00:09:46,433
Sir Justin?

185
00:09:47,367 --> 00:09:48,767
Let's go.

186
00:09:49,467 --> 00:09:50,767
[RAPHIE] Excuse me.

187
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,533
[SARI] Ms. Trixie.

188
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:01,867
[SARI] Eat first.

189
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:05,433
[RAPHIE] Cheska.

190
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,933
[SARI] Sir Gio.

191
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:18,100
Water, sir.

192
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:22,733
Thank you.

193
00:10:28,167 --> 00:10:29,600
[SARI] Sir Martin.

194
00:10:30,767 --> 00:10:32,067
Eat first.

195
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,867
- Sari...
- Sir.

196
00:10:35,033 --> 00:10:37,600
I'm the one who will worry
if you don't eat.

197
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:40,167
Please.

198
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:44,000
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

199
00:10:44,133 --> 00:10:45,167
[RAPHIE] Your water, sir.

200
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:48,033
Thank you.

201
00:10:48,167 --> 00:10:51,167
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

202
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,733
Eat first.

203
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:56,800
Thanks.

204
00:10:57,933 --> 00:10:59,667
Come on,
we have a long day ahead.

205
00:11:00,967 --> 00:11:02,133
I'm good. Thank you.

206
00:11:02,267 --> 00:11:03,500
[GIO] Justin.

207
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,900
- Jade.
- Gio, I'm alright.

208
00:11:10,067 --> 00:11:11,200
Come on.

209
00:11:14,567 --> 00:11:15,867
Thank you.

210
00:11:18,533 --> 00:11:19,933
[LUNA SIGHS]

211
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:23,433
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:25,000
You haven't eaten yet.

213
00:11:26,167 --> 00:11:27,200
I'm fine.

214
00:11:28,133 --> 00:11:29,500
Come on.

215
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:31,900
I'm not hungry, Gio.

216
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:41,433
- Thank you.
- Even if you just drink.

217
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:48,600
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

218
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:10,567
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

219
00:12:19,233 --> 00:12:20,500
[POLICE 1] Syvera.

220
00:12:21,267 --> 00:12:22,833
We checked the perimeter.

221
00:12:22,967 --> 00:12:25,067
It looks like they've
already gotten away.

222
00:12:27,367 --> 00:12:28,700
I have a bad feeling about this.

223
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:33,633
All the murders are near
the Hotel 88 property.

224
00:12:35,233 --> 00:12:37,833
How does the criminal manage
to get onto the island?

225
00:12:37,967 --> 00:12:40,600
It might be intentional,
so we stop looking elsewhere.

226
00:12:40,733 --> 00:12:42,167
Look around again.

227
00:12:43,967 --> 00:12:45,133
Okay, sir.

228
00:12:45,267 --> 00:12:52,100
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:12:59,133 --> 00:13:00,367
<i> Something's wrong.</i>

230
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:02,267
<i>It wasn't an outsider
who did this.</i>

231
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:05,567
[GUN CLANKS]

232
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:12,733
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

233
00:13:26,733 --> 00:13:28,233
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

234
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,633
Lord...

235
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:36,533
please save Leon and Kiko...

236
00:13:36,667 --> 00:13:38,800
from the pain...

237
00:13:38,933 --> 00:13:40,700
<i>- and from dangers...
- [MACHINE BEEPS]</i>

238
00:13:40,833 --> 00:13:42,833
[FRIDA] beyond our reach.

239
00:13:42,967 --> 00:13:44,733
[DOCTOR] Set to 200 joules.

240
00:13:44,867 --> 00:13:46,033
- Clear?
- [NURSE] Clear.

241
00:13:46,167 --> 00:13:47,700
[DEFIBRILLATOR THUMPS]

242
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:50,033
[MACHINE BEEPS]

243
00:13:50,167 --> 00:13:52,167
[FRIDA]<i> If someone needs
</i> to be taken...

244
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,700
<i> let it be me.</i>

245
00:13:55,267 --> 00:13:57,400
- [FRIDA]<i> Take my life instead,
</i>- [DEFIBRILLATOR THUMPS]

246
00:13:57,533 --> 00:13:59,600
<i> not my sons.</i>

247
00:13:59,733 --> 00:14:06,700
- [EKG MACHINE FLATLINES]
- [SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:15,133
<i> They're both fighting.</i>

249
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:18,767
<i>Please give them the strength
they currently don't have.</i>

250
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:25,067
<i>Do not let us wake up
in a world without them.</i>

251
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:32,033
[SOLEMN MUSIC CONTINUES]

252
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,100
[DOOR OPENS]

253
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:35,667
Mrs. Almazan.

254
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:37,400
Endayas.

255
00:14:41,567 --> 00:14:42,833
I'm sorry.

256
00:14:42,967 --> 00:14:45,300
We will only talk
to the families.

257
00:14:45,433 --> 00:14:47,200
We're all the family members.

258
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:51,800
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:54,200
We did the best we could.

260
00:14:54,933 --> 00:14:56,633
But that's about it.

261
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,500
- I'm very sorry.
- No...

262
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:01,200
[CRYING] What?

263
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,600
- Doc...
- Doc!

264
00:15:04,733 --> 00:15:06,833
Doc, maybe there's
another way...

265
00:15:07,633 --> 00:15:09,200
Doc...

266
00:15:10,033 --> 00:15:16,900
[CRYING]

267
00:15:18,667 --> 00:15:20,167
Wait!

268
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:23,133
Maybe... there's still
something we can do?

269
00:15:23,267 --> 00:15:25,700
Nope! Nope! Mom!

270
00:15:27,067 --> 00:15:29,433
[JADE] Please... Please...
Please...

271
00:15:30,133 --> 00:15:33,767
[CRYING]

272
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:38,000
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

273
00:15:39,867 --> 00:15:42,633
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

274
00:15:42,767 --> 00:15:49,633
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

275
00:15:52,867 --> 00:15:53,767
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN]

276
00:15:55,067 --> 00:16:01,900
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

277
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:11,733
[JADE SOBBING]

278
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:14,200
Leon!

279
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:18,200
- [JADE] Leon!
- [JUSTIN SOBBING]

280
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:21,367
- [LUNA] Leon! Leon!
- Leon!

281
00:16:22,067 --> 00:16:23,800
[JADE] Leon! Wake up!

282
00:16:23,933 --> 00:16:26,600
- Leon, please!
- Leon!

283
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:30,333
[JADE] Leon, wake up! Leon!

284
00:16:30,467 --> 00:16:33,433
- No! Leon!
- [JUSTIN SOBBING]

285
00:16:34,533 --> 00:16:36,367
Leon!

286
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:42,167
[JADE] Leon!

287
00:16:42,967 --> 00:16:45,300
- Leon!
- [JUSTIN SOBBING]

288
00:16:46,367 --> 00:16:49,633
- [LUNA] Leon, wake up! Leon!
- [JADE SOBBING]

289
00:16:49,767 --> 00:16:52,900
[JADE] Leon, wake up!
Leon, please!

290
00:16:53,033 --> 00:16:59,833
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

291
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,333
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

292
00:17:03,467 --> 00:17:04,400
[CHESKA SNIFFLES]

293
00:17:04,533 --> 00:17:06,267
- Ma.
- [GIO] Auntie.

294
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,767
What happened to your brother?

295
00:17:10,967 --> 00:17:14,800
Martin and Gio said...

296
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:18,633
Someone they didn't know
attacked them.

297
00:17:21,067 --> 00:17:22,900
[CRYING SOFTLY]

298
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:24,233
Ma, I'm sorry.

299
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,633
I'm sorry. Kiko got in danger
because of me.

300
00:17:27,767 --> 00:17:28,633
Shh!

301
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:32,700
Shh. Don't say that.

302
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:34,333
It's not your fault.

303
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:36,600
The bastard...

304
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:39,067
- It's that bastard's fault.
- [CHESKA] I'm sorry.

305
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:41,667
[CRYING, SNIFFLING]

306
00:17:44,067 --> 00:17:45,133
[CHESKA] I'm sorry.

307
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:46,767
[CHESKA BREATHES DEEPLY]

308
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:48,233
[GEORGINA] Kiko, my son...

309
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,733
Wake up, son. Mama is here.

310
00:17:51,867 --> 00:17:55,767
I will take care of you.
Your sister is here too.

311
00:17:56,733 --> 00:17:58,900
Your brothers are here too,
Kiko, please.

312
00:17:59,033 --> 00:18:00,000
Please.

313
00:18:00,867 --> 00:18:04,467
I'll take care of you, Kiko.
Wake up, please.

314
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:08,400
Kiko, wake up. Please.

315
00:18:09,067 --> 00:18:10,000
[CRYING]

316
00:18:10,133 --> 00:18:12,000
- Please?
- [CHESKA] Bro...

317
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:14,900
Wake up, bro.

318
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:17,600
Bro, wake up.

319
00:18:17,733 --> 00:18:20,000
[CRYING]

320
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:22,700
Wake up for me and Mama, bro.

321
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:24,933
- Come on, bro.
- [GEORGINA] Son...

322
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:27,600
Promise me...

323
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:29,067
Promise me.

324
00:18:30,267 --> 00:18:32,067
You're going to fight.

325
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,667
You're not going
to give up, okay?

326
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:38,800
You have to fight. Please.
You have to fight. You can't--

327
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:41,133
You can't give up, son.

328
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:42,467
[CRYING]

329
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:45,167
You can't give up.

330
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:46,933
[GEORGINA SOBBING]

331
00:18:47,067 --> 00:18:53,900
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

332
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:57,533
[CHESKA] Come on,
wake up, bro.

333
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:02,267
Bro.

334
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:09,400
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

335
00:19:11,967 --> 00:19:14,667
[CRYING, SNIFFLING]

336
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,333
He's not okay.

337
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:20,100
He has a lot of injuries.

338
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:23,133
Your brother struggled.

339
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:30,067
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

340
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:31,633
[HUSHED] Leon...

341
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:35,567
He was alone.

342
00:19:37,667 --> 00:19:40,300
He suffered alone.

343
00:19:40,433 --> 00:19:46,667
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

344
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,600
[FRIDA] Are you doing okay here?

345
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:50,567
[LEON] I'm alright, Ma.

346
00:19:53,367 --> 00:19:54,500
[FRIDA CRYING]

347
00:19:54,633 --> 00:20:01,633
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

348
00:20:03,967 --> 00:20:06,067
[LEON]<i> We should protect
</i> each other.

349
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:13,033
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

350
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:22,333
[JADE CRYING]

351
00:20:22,467 --> 00:20:29,533
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

352
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:35,100
[LEON] I'm sorry.

353
00:20:36,967 --> 00:20:38,200
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

354
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:42,700
<i>I tried to protect all of you,
so I kept this all to myself.</i>

355
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:50,633
[JUSTIN CRYING]

356
00:20:53,367 --> 00:20:55,267
[LEON] Just imagine it's lit up.

357
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,833
[JADE] Wow!

358
00:20:56,967 --> 00:20:58,767
[LEON]<i> We're the only men left
</i> in the family.

359
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:01,200
<i> We have to protect our family.</i>

360
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:02,433
<i> That's why you need...</i>

361
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:06,767
<i> ...to fix your life, Justin.</i>

362
00:21:08,733 --> 00:21:09,900
[JUSTIN SNIFFLES]

363
00:21:12,433 --> 00:21:14,767
[JUSTIN CRYING]

364
00:21:16,133 --> 00:21:17,200
I'm sorry.

365
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:21,733
I'm sorry
I wasn't with you, Leon...

366
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:26,633
...when you were struggling.

367
00:21:29,567 --> 00:21:31,033
I'm sorry...

368
00:21:31,167 --> 00:21:37,667
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

369
00:21:38,467 --> 00:21:39,567
[SMOOCHES]

370
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:48,400
- [SNIFFLES, SOBS SOFTLY]
- [WHIMPERS]

371
00:21:48,533 --> 00:21:51,433
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

372
00:21:51,567 --> 00:21:53,167
[COUGHS]

373
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,833
[SOBBING, WHIMPERING]

374
00:21:57,967 --> 00:22:00,833
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

375
00:22:00,967 --> 00:22:02,000
[JUSTIN] Mom...

376
00:22:02,133 --> 00:22:05,467
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

377
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,333
They're going
to take care of Leon.

378
00:22:07,467 --> 00:22:10,933
- [EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SNIFFLING]

379
00:22:11,067 --> 00:22:12,333
Mom.

380
00:22:13,533 --> 00:22:14,533
No.

381
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:19,333
- [SNIFFLING]
- [WHIMPERING]

382
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:23,500
[JUSTIN, FRIDA SOBBING LOUDLY]

383
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:26,667
Leon!

384
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:28,167
- Leon!
- Leon...

385
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:33,533
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

386
00:22:33,667 --> 00:22:34,733
[JUSTIN] Leon...

387
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:38,833
[FRIDA] I'm sorry...

388
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:44,433
- [SOBBING CONTINUES]
- [EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

389
00:22:44,567 --> 00:22:45,767
Leon.

390
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:47,000
No.

391
00:22:47,133 --> 00:22:49,100
Mom. Please.

392
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:50,400
- Mom...
- No.

393
00:22:50,533 --> 00:22:53,367
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

394
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:58,900
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

395
00:22:59,033 --> 00:23:00,500
[WHIMPERING]

396
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:02,333
[JUSTIN SOBBING LOUDLY]

397
00:23:02,467 --> 00:23:05,500
[LUNA, JADE SOBBING]

398
00:23:06,667 --> 00:23:07,900
Please...

399
00:23:09,467 --> 00:23:12,100
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

400
00:23:12,233 --> 00:23:13,467
[VOICE TREMBLING]
L-Leon...

401
00:23:14,367 --> 00:23:16,400
Luna. Luna, let's go!

402
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:18,267
Come on, let's go!

403
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:21,300
- Come on! This way!
- What about Leon? No...

404
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:24,567
- We can't leave him!
- [JUSTIN SOBBING LOUDLY]

405
00:23:24,733 --> 00:23:26,400
[LUNA SOBBING]

406
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:28,500
[WAILS] Leon!

407
00:23:30,333 --> 00:23:32,000
<i>All hotel operations
are suspended right now.</i>

408
00:23:32,133 --> 00:23:34,400
<i>We're closing the hotel
to keep everyone safe.</i>

409
00:23:34,533 --> 00:23:37,300
<i>Mom said only family
can be here for now.</i>

410
00:23:37,433 --> 00:23:40,133
<i> You said he'd be fine.</i>

411
00:23:40,267 --> 00:23:42,700
<i> You said he'd come home to us.</i>

412
00:23:42,833 --> 00:23:44,100
<i> You lied!</i>

413
00:23:44,233 --> 00:23:45,633
[SCREAMING]
<i> You're an idiot, Martin!</i>

414
00:23:45,767 --> 00:23:47,000
<i>You want to get hurt?
[BLOW LANDS] Fine, take this!</i>

415
00:23:47,133 --> 00:23:50,933
<i>Stop punishing yourself,
honor Leon and get justice!</i>

416
00:23:51,067 --> 00:23:52,533
<i>It seems the person
you're up against is sharp.</i>

417
00:23:52,667 --> 00:23:54,667
<i> The only lead we have is Kiko.</i>

418
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,767
<i>But there's no telling
when he will wake up.</i>
